haue the cupp of his bloud which is incorruptible loue and life euerlasting. If the cuppe of Christes bloud be incorruptible charity and life euerlasting, then is it the effect of Christes bloud, that Ignatius speaketh of, and not his naturall bloud, which is the cause thereof. Other prooues then these, Sander hath not in this Chapter for his purpose, which prooue it nothing at all.
               
               
